category=Getting Started
description=<p>The Multiple Choice Questionnaire allows you to create your own multiple choice quiz or test.  This application is capable of saving its results to a file or uploading them to an ftp server.  The application comes in two parts, the quiz stacks themselves, and an editor stack.  The editor stack demonstrates how you can easily create one application which modifies another.  It also shows how to create your own custom (or &#147;virtual&#148;) object properties.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The Video Tutorial shows you how to use this Sample Project, and how to take it apart to understand how it works or copy portions of it for use in your own applications.  The PDF contains the same information as the Video, in printable form.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Lucida Grande" size="11"><a href="video:Multiple Choice Questionnaire">Click here to go the the corresponding video and PDF</a></font></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Lucida Grande">We recommend you to have explored the introductory video tutorials so you have a basic understanding of how Revolution works before you start on the Sample Projects.</font></p>
level=3
name=Multiple Choice Questionnaire
title=Multiple Choice Questionnaire - for online learning
topics=<p>The key topics covered in this Project are:</p>\n<p>   - Using multiple stacks in one project</p>\n<p>   - Creating a custom editor palette to edit a quiz</p>\n<p>   - Using &quot;virtual&quot; or custom properties to store state information</p>\n<p>   - Uploading text to an FTP site and handling basic errors</p>\n<p>   - Hiding and showing objects when necessary</p>\n<p>   - Changing fields from editable to not editable by script</p>\n<p>   - Keeping track and constructing a message with the quiz score</p>